---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---

<Base
  title="About — Nous Ergon"
  description="Nous Ergon is an applied AI lab — intelligence at work. We build agentic systems against problems with measurable, continuously verifiable outcomes."
>
  <section class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-6 pt-16 pb-12">
    <h1 class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-semibold text-zinc-100 mb-2">Nous Ergon</h1>
    <p class="text-sm text-zinc-500 mb-8">
      &nu;&omicron;&upsilon;&sigmaf; &epsilon;&rho;&gamma;&omicron;&nu; &mdash; <em>intelligence at work</em>
    </p>

    <h2 class="text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-wider text-sky-400 mb-3">The lab</h2>
    <p class="text-sm md:text-base text-zinc-300 leading-relaxed mb-4">
      Nous Ergon is an applied AI lab. We build agentic systems against
      problems with measurable, continuously verifiable outcomes &mdash; and
      instrument every decision they make. The work spans two products and a
      set of open-source tools.
    </p>
    <p class="text-sm md:text-base text-zinc-300 leading-relaxed mb-8">
      <strong class="text-zinc-100">Crucible</strong> is the experiment
      harness: a system for rigorous AI/ML experiments in finance, running
      live. <strong class="text-zinc-100">Metron</strong> is multi-broker
      portfolio analytics. The lab also maintains open-source tools &mdash;
      mnemon, flow-doctor, morning-signal &mdash; built for our own work and
      released where they generalize.
    </p>

    <h2 class="text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-wider text-sky-400 mb-3">The name</h2>
    <p class="text-sm md:text-base text-zinc-300 leading-relaxed mb-4">
      <strong class="text-zinc-100">Nous Ergon</strong> &mdash; Greek for <em>intelligence at work</em>
      (&nu;&omicron;&upsilon;&sigmaf; &epsilon;&rho;&gamma;&omicron;&nu;,
      pronounced <em>noose air-gone</em>).
    </p>
    <p class="text-sm md:text-base text-zinc-300 leading-relaxed mb-8">
      <em>Nous</em> (&nu;&omicron;&upsilon;&sigmaf;) is mind, intellect, the capacity for reason.
      <em>Ergon</em> (&epsilon;&rho;&gamma;&omicron;&nu;) is work, deed, function &mdash; the same root as
      English <em>ergonomics</em> and <em>energy</em>. The name frames what the lab does:
      agentic intelligence applied to measurable, continuously verifiable problems.
      The work &mdash; the <em>ergon</em> &mdash; is what's on display.
    </p>

    <h2 class="text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-wider text-sky-400 mb-3">How we build</h2>
    <p class="text-sm md:text-base text-zinc-300 leading-relaxed mb-8">
      Founded by
      <a class="text-sky-400 hover:text-sky-300 transition" href="/founder">Brian McMahon</a>
      in March 2026. AI-augmented engineering is core to the lab's method
      &mdash; <strong class="text-zinc-100">Claude Code</strong> (Anthropic's
      LLM coding assistant) is an active collaborator on every implementation
      pass, and the systems themselves are a demonstration of how far that
      method scales.
    </p>

    <h2 class="text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-wider text-sky-400 mb-3">Contact</h2>
    <ul class="text-sm md:text-base text-zinc-300 space-y-1">
      <li><a class="text-sky-400 hover:text-sky-300 transition" href="mailto:nous@nousergon.ai">nous@nousergon.ai</a></li>
      <li><a class="text-sky-400 hover:text-sky-300 transition" href="https://github.com/cipher813">GitHub</a></li>
    </ul>
  </section>
</Base>
